For Mefisto, nu is the value of the coefficient of Delta u_i, for any i,
where u_i is the i-th component of the velocity.

Cf http://hypertextbook.com/physics/matter/viscosity/

The simple viscosity is noted eta in pascal second [Pa.s] or millipascal second  [mPa.s].

The kinematic viscosity, noted nu, is the ratio between eta and rho in square meter per second [m^2/s].

The notation nu(X) shows the possible dependence at point X=(x,y,z)

The order of 6 parameters of the USER's function VISCOSITY
at time TIME, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLSVO of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT )
the directory number NO_OBJECT
must be

VISCOSITY( TIME, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_OBJECT, NO_OBJECT ) 

and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)

All these parameters will be initialized during its call.
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of the VISCOSITY of the FLUID
 
EXAMPLE:
deffunc viscos( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, material ) ;
if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'water' )
then viscos=0.001;
else if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'blood' )
     then viscos=0.0035;
     else viscos=0 ;
     endif;  
endif;
endfunc; 

Remark: the LU function nuobjt( p1, p2 ) gives the
number of the PLSVO of type p1 with the name p2.
